<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL REPORT WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
UCLA; 
</P>
<P>
MADDOX (353) PASSES ALL BUT BONO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAL FLORENCE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Even though UCLA lost to Michigan, 38-15, Saturday, quarterback Tommy Maddox 
had some impressive statistics. 
</P>
<P>
The redshirt freshman, starting for the first time, completed 26 of 47 passes 
for 353 yards. 
</P>
<P>
The yardage was the second-highest total in UCLA history, behind Steve Bono's 
399 yards passing against Brigham Young in 1983. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA wide receiver Scott Miller, linebacker Rocen Keeton and defensive tackle 
Brian Kelly, all injured, aren't expected to play Saturday against Washington 
State, although there is a possibility that Miller might play. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA Coach Terry Donahue said that wide receiver Paul Richardson is still 
bothered by an ankle injury. However, strong safety Matt Darby, who missed the 
Michigan game with a shoulder injury, and nose guard Garrett Greedy, who has 
also been injured, are expected to play. MAL FLORENCE 
</P>
</TEXT>
