NEWSWIRE: HOLYFIELD-FOREMAN FIGHT IN THE WORKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A heavyweight title fight between Evander Holyfield and George Foreman is in 
the works -- if Holyfield dethrones undisputed champion Buster Douglas on Oct. 
25 and Foreman continues to beat his unheralded opponents, Newsday reported. 
</P>
<P>
According to promoter Bob Arum, "an agreement in principle" for such a fight 
has been reached, as long as the two heavyweights keep up their ends of the 
bargain. 
</P>
<P>
Tonight Foreman (68-2, 64 knockouts) will earn $250,000 to fight Terry Anderson 
(19-3, 17 knockouts) in a 10-round bout at the London Arena. 
