<DATELINE>
<P>
HOUSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Kings scored two power-play goals in the second period and went on to beat 
the Pittsburgh Penguins, 4-1, in an NHL exhibition game Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
Veteran defenseman Larry Robinson scored with a 15-foot shot from the slot, 
assisted by Tomas Sandstrom and Rob Blake, at 8:14 of the second period. 
</P>
<P>
The Kings made it 2-0 before a Houston Summit crowd of 10,413 when they had a 
two-man advantage, and Sandstrom punched a shot in from the goal mouth at 
10:21. 
</P>
<P>
The Kings made it 3-0 with an unassisted short-handed goal by Brad Jones at 
8:54 of the third period. Luc Robitaille scored the Kings' final goal in the 
third period. 
</P>
<P>
John Cullen scored for Pittsburgh. 
</P>
