<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: WOMEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UC San Diego and Cal State Dominguez Hills played to a 0-0 tie in a 
nonconference game at Dominguez Hills. Goalkeepers Karin Carper, UCSD, saved 
seven shots and Jennifer Lueck, CSDH, saved six. 
</P>
<P>
Dominguez Hills (3-4-1) finished second in Division II last year and was the 
only team to defeat the defending Division III national champion Tritons 
(5-1-1). 
</P>
