<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL REPORT WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
SAN DIEGO STATE; 
</P>
<P>
LUGINBILL SHUFFLES DEFENSIVE BACKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the wake of Ty Detmer's 514-yard passing exhibition Saturday -- the most 
passing yards ever allowed by an Aztec defense -- San Diego State Coach Al 
Luginbill has decided to make some personnel changes for Saturday's home game 
against Air Force. 
</P>
<P>
After practice Monday, Luginbill announced these moves: 
</P>
<P>
 -- Junior Tracey Mao replaces junior Derrick Williams as the starting nickel 
back. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Senior Morey Paul will back up Mao, and Williams moves out of the two-man 
rotation. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Sophomore Robert Griffith will start at dime back, and he will be backed up 
by sophomore Zac Stokes, who has been out with a shoulder injury since the 
preseason. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Senior Marlon Andrews and sophomore Gary Taylor will remain as the starting 
cornerbacks, but sophomore Damon Piere and sophomore Darrell Lewis will now 
play behind them. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Senior Clark Moses, a second-team all-WAC defensive back last year, had 
been playing on the second team, but he has been demoted to the scout team. 
</P>
<P>
Injuries to running backs Tommy Booker and Curtis Butts have left the Aztecs 
with two healthy backs (Kipp Jeffries and T.C. Wright) and have forced 
Luginbill to move H-back Larry Maxey to running back. Butts (neck strain) and 
Booker (ankle) are questionable for Saturday. Luginbill said he does not yet 
know who will start at running back. . . . Freshman linebacker Jamal Duff 
(thigh bruise) is improved and has been listed as questionable. DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<CORRECTION-DATE>
<P>
September 26, 1990, Wednesday, San Diego County Edition 
</P>
</CORRECTION-DATE>
<CORRECTION>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
<P>
SDSU cornerbacks -- A story Tuesday incorrectly reported the backup players at 
cornerback on San Diego State's football team. Freshman John Louis and 
sophomore Damon Pieri are the backups. 
</P>
</CORRECTION>
