<P>
DU PONT TURKISH PLANT BEGINS PRODUCTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WILMINGTON, Del. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Du Pont Co. said production has started at a new industrial plant in Ismit, 
Turkey capable of producing up to 50 million pounds of nylon annually. 
</P>
<P>
The plant is part of D-USA, a 50-50 joint venture between Du Pont and the 
Sabanci Group, a leading Turkish industrial company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
