<BYLINE>
<P>
By Michael Flagg and Mark Landsbaum 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WAR'S WAKE: You won't see Orange County in PBS' acclaimed Civil War documentary 
this week, but the war had an effect here: It made possible the massive Irvine 
Ranch. . . . At war's end, cotton trade with the South was so disrupted that 
demand for wool skyrocketed. Four ranchers bought land here to graze sheep, and 
one, James Irvine, above, eventually bought out the others and wound up owning 
a fifth of the county's territory. Irvine's heirs later began development, most 
notably in the city that bears his name. Michael Flagg and Mark Landsbaum 
</P>
