<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; 
</P>
<P>
NEW LAW EXPECTED TO HELP COMBAT FRAUD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM McQUEENEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A new weapon to combat fraudulent telephone-sales and investment schemes may be 
coming to the city. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council tonight is expected to pass a law requiring anyone who wants 
to operate an investment or telephone-sales company in Irvine to fill out an 
extra page of information about their business and themselves to receive a 
business license. 
</P>
<P>
"The form will give us more information on these companies, and it will make 
them jump through the hoops, so to speak, so we can determine if they are 
legitimate," Police Sgt. David Freedland said. 
</P>
<P>
The form requires applicants to divulge whether they are registered with 
various state and federal agencies regulating investment companies, whether the 
owner of the business has been convicted of fraud-related offenses and whether 
the business operates out of a post-office box or postal center. Y 
</P>
</TEXT>
