ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LA PALMA; 
</P>
<P>
BOY FREED OF CHARGE IN PLAYMATE'S DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JERRY HICKS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At the request of the victim's mother, Orange County prosecutors on Monday 
dismissed criminal charges against a 12-year-old La Palma boy accused of the 
fatal shooting of his best friend. 
</P>
<P>
The boy, who faced charges of involuntary manslaughter, was scheduled to go on 
trial Monday before Superior Court Judge William F. Rylaarsdam. 
</P>
<P>
But Deputy Dist. Atty. Brent F. Romney said that he discussed the case with the 
victim's mother, Paula LaFortune, and learned she did not want the prosecution 
to continue. 
</P>
<P>
The critical issue, Romney said, was whether the youth had the knowledge that 
what he was doing could be dangerous. 
</P>
<P>
"The victim's mother told us that the two boys were so close, he would never 
have pointed the gun at her son if he'd known he could have hurt him," Romney 
said. "She said this boy had suffered enough for what he'd done and she hoped 
we would not go forward." JERRY HICKS 
