SYSTEM INDUSTRIES MAKES DEAL TO SELL DATABASE 'ACCELERATOR' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Anaheim-based System Industries Inc. said it has formed a strategic marketing 
agreement with Charles River Data Systems of Framingham, Mass. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement, which is valued at more than $35 million for the first three 
years, calls for System Industries to sell Charles River's relational 
accelerator, a database enhancement system for the Digital Equipment Corp. 
computer market. 
