<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: ROME; 
</P>
<P>
16 DAYS OF NATO WAR GAMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A major 16-day military exercise involving eight member nations of the North 
Atlantic Treaty Organization begins in northwestern Italy on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The maneuvers involve about 10,000 troops in a combined land, sea and air 
exercise called Operation Display Determination. Nations participating are the 
United States, Britain, France, West Germany, Italy, Portugal, Spain and 
Turkey. 
</P>
<P>
NATO officers insist that the maneuver has no connection with the Persian Gulf 
crisis. "It was planned long before the Iraqi invasion of Kuwait," a spokesman 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
MILITARY MANEUVERS; NORTH ATLANTIC TREATY ORGANIZATION 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
