<P>
QUAYLE THANKS MARINES' KIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Vice President Dan Quayle, arriving today at El Toro Marine Corps Air Station 
for a day of campaigning in Orange County, thanked the families of soldiers 
deployed to Saudi Arabia and delivered a message from President Bush. 
</P>
<P>
"Thank you for helping us keep peace in the Middle East," he told a crowd of 
about 3,000, including students of MacArthur Intermediate School in Santa Ana, 
many of them children of the deployed Marines. 
</P>
<P>
Quayle arrived at the Marine base from Ontario aboard Air Force 2 about 11:50 
this morning. 
