P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
BARCLAYS TO TEAM UP WITH BA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Barclays Bank, Britain's largest, said today it would form a partnership with 
San Francisco-based BankAmerica Corp. in a joint traveler's check operation. 
</P>
<P>
Under terms of the agreement, BankAmerica acquires a majority stake in 
Interpayment Services Ltd., a Barclays Bank traveler's check service, a 
Barclays spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The move, which will create one of the largest traveler's check issuing 
operations, appears aimed at challenging American Express' dominance of the 
market, analysts said. 
</P>
<P>
"We are poised to challenge anyone in the world marketplace," said T. R. Mock, 
president of BA Cheque, the BankAmerica subsidiary responsible for European 
traveler's check operations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
