<HEADLINE>
<P>
PAPER TO REPLACE PLASTIC FILM CANISTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The makers of Fuji film said today they will replace the plastic canisters in 
which their film is sold in the United States with paper ones as an 
environmental measure. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, Fuji Photo Film U.S.A. Inc. said most Fuji film boxes will be made 
from recycled paper. 
</P>
<P>
The new film canisters are made of moisture-proof paper that the Japanese 
company said it developed with its own technology. It said the containers 
provide the same protection as plastic ones. 
</P>
</TEXT>
