<P>
PRIZED 7-FOOTER PICKS KANSAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DUNCANVILLE, Tex. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Greg Ostertag, the most highly recruited basketball player in Texas, says he 
has orally committed to attending the University of Kansas. 
</P>
<P>
Ostertag, a 7-1 center at Duncanville High School, made the announcement 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
"I liked the coaches, the players, the campus -- pretty much everything about 
it," Ostertag said. "The atmosphere and the program were just too much to turn 
down." 
</P>
<P>
Ostertag, who averaged 15 points and 13 rebounds last season as a junior, said 
he will sign a letter of intent with the Jayhawks on Nov. 14, the first day of 
the NCAA's early signing period for basketball. He visited Kansas two weeks 
ago. 
</P>
