<P>
VAUGHN CHOOSES MEMPHIS STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MEMPHIS, Tenn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Whites Creek High School center David Vaughn has announced he will play college 
basketball for his uncle, Memphis State Coach Larry Finch. 
</P>
<P>
The 6-foot-9 Vaughn, considered one of the nation's top 10 recruits, chose 
Finch and the Tigers over Syracuse, DePaul, Arizona State, UCLA, Tennessee, 
Virginia and Kentucky. He is entering his senior year of high school. 
</P>
<P>
The All-State performer averaged 20 points, 12.4 rebounds and five blocked 
shots his junior year, leading the Cobras (34-1) to the semifinal round of the 
Class AAA state basketball tournament. 
</P>
