<P>
HIGHLIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HENRY ELLARD 
</P>
<P>
It started out like a record-breaking day: An 11-yard diving catch in front of 
Ben Smith, next a 15-yard reception between Jessie Small and Eric Allen, then, 
isolated on a linebacker, a 50-yard scoring pass play. Three Jim Everett 
passes, three Henry Ellard catches for 76 yards and a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
A fierce Philadelphia pass rush followed, ending the Ram loss. Still, Ellard 
finished with seven receptions for 145 yards, bringing his three-game totals to 
17 catches for 313 yards and two touchdowns. 
</P>
